The last few months have been tough on Roman.
 Clawing his way to one of the top journalists wasn't an easy rode but he didn't regret a single minute of it. In the end it was all woth it. Not only was his last entry a roaring success but his boss asked him to fil in for him at the gala. To say Roman was thrilled would be an understatemnt.
 Luck was finally on his side.

There was only one issue Roman had to solve before goin out for the evening. And that was his clothing choice.
 Call him shallow but according to Roman first impression were very important. He became rocognizable due to his clothing always being adored by something red. Be it the suit itself, a scarf or a hat. But the party throwewrs deceided to make a sea themed party due to some important marine officer attending it.
 That left Roman with the choice whether he should choose his usual getup and stend out or blend in with his more tonned down grean suit.

After much delibaration the journalist finaly decided to wear the green suit. It's not his usual color but he has to admit it does bring out his eyes. As much as he likes to stand out maybe waring something in tune with the dress code will highten his chances of securing some interviews. Adjusting his tie Roman notices the time.
 'SH*T' he swears loudly trying to tie the tie faster but only managing it to tangle it.
 There is no way he's gonna make it on time, unless he's gonna take a shortcut through the notorious Crystal therithory. He's be like a walking target.
 Then again he'd prefer to be punctual to his first important Gala.
 Is his life really worth risking making a good first impression?

You jump into the strangers car. If he wanted to shoot you he would have done so while your back was turned to him you reason. Just as you are about to thank him the man speaks up.
 'You gotta watch your back Rem. Pat will have your head if I'll have to drag your wounded body to his clinic again.'

The mans eyes widen and he takes a closer look at you.
 'Oh crap! You're not Remus!' He says before he takes a sharp U turn rushing back.
 A figure in green jumps onto the road and the driver stops just a few centemeters short of hitting him. As soon as they stop the figure rips the passenger seat open.
 Their eyes widden momentarily before they squeez themselves net to Roman. The driver starts the car before the door fully closses. The sounds of bullets chaisng them.

The man gives him a strange look.
 'Did you hit your head or something?' He reaches out his hand for Romans forehead and Roman bats it away.
 'Hey I'm greatfull and all but I think you've got me mixed up with somebody'

'If you wanted to ditch me you should have done so for someone more handsome then me, Vee.' The man in green states. Is this guy insane? The driver-Vee laughs at the statement. 'You're not setting the bar very hight'
 'You wound me' The man gasps dramatically and slides slightly down the seat, earning himself a chuckle from Vee, who turn to Roman. 'Sorry for accidentally kindnapping you. Where should we drop you off?'

Vee smiles a smile that's just a bit unnerving.
 'Think of us as chofeurs for the night' Roman decides it's wise not to press the matter.
 'To the gala then if you don't mind mr. V' Remus snickers at the nickname and Vee just rolls his eyes. They drop him off a block away from the party. Normally Roman would argue but Vee just saved his life and shot a man in front of him so he decided not to press his luck. He walks the few meters.

Dr.Picani is a man of many trades. Career-wise he is a phycologist but due to his friendly personality and outgoing demeenor he has soon become a public figure. He has led many charities and the town people adore him.
 Popularity runs in the Picani family as his child, Elliot, manages one of the most, if not the most, popular newspapers in the city- The Cartoonist. Roman would kill to be employed by them to prove his worth as a journalist.
 Dr. Picani has stayed away from politics up until this year when he decided to run for the Major office. He is the only candidat that poses a threat to the re-election of Janus.

Dr. Picani stands together with the famous marine admiral and a few other gentle-man. Roman decides to approach them.
 They did not call Roman prince charming in school for nothing as he flawlessly joins the conversation and slowly brings the atention to himself. Picani offers him a trial period at The Cartoonist.
Well i do have a stable job- the future of Romans newspaper hangs on his shoulders.

Roman secures an interview not only with Picani but also with the General.
 Picani get's elected as major and with sweat and tears of Roman and his collegues their newspaper becomes recognisable all over the state
This is the oportunity Roman has been hoping for and he accepts it in a heartbeat.
